<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05008a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05008a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05008a"> 8(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> wilful lie of priest = / sacrilege (sacr. lips)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[After telling a lie, St. Assicus, appointed Bishop of Elphin by St. Patrick, went into solitude]</font> the Bishop declared himself unworthy ever again to exercise his pontifical office, since from his <mark>lips</mark> had proceded <mark>a wilful lie</mark>, which, coming <mark>from a priest</mark>, the sacred canons declare to be a <mark>sacrilege</mark>. <small> William Bullen Morris, <a name="WBML" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WBML"><cite title="source">The Life of Saint Patrick Apostle of Ireland</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1890) 234</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
